.Dd 2026-07-20
.Dt XBGCD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm xbgcd
.Nd X background color daemon that cycles the root window through interpolated colors
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl v
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
slowly cycles the root window background through a sequence of RGB colors,
interpolating between consecutive steps.
Once started it runs forever, repainting the root window every
.Ar delay
milliseconds.
.Pp
At each iteration
.Nm
computes a color by linearly interpolating between the previous step and the
current one, advancing a sub-step counter by
.Ar sub_step_inc .
When the counter exceeds 1.0 the current step becomes the previous one and the
next step in the sequence is selected (wrapping around to the first).
.Pp
Colors are allocated via
.Xr XAllocColor 3 ,
so anything accepted by
.Xr XParseColor 3
would in principle work, but
.Nm
formats them as
.Li #RRGGBB
itself.
.Pp
On
.Ox ,
.Nm
calls
.Xr pledge 2
with
.Qq stdio
after opening the display.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl v
Print version information to stderr and exit.
.El
.Sh CONFIGURATION
.Nm
is customized by editing
.Pa config.h
and recompiling \(em the suckless convention.
The available knobs are:
.Bl -tag -width "sub_step_inc" -compact
.It Sy steps
Array of
.Li struct MyColor
triplets
.Pq Li { r , g , b }
in the range
.Sq 0.0
to
.Sq 1.0
that
.Nm
cycles through.
.It Sy initial_color
.Li struct MyColor
used as the
.Qq previous
color for the very first interpolation.
.It Sy sub_step_inc
Float in the range
.Sq (0.0 , 1.0]
added to the sub-step counter on every iteration; smaller values produce a
slower, smoother transition.
.It Sy delay
Unsigned integer; milliseconds slept between iterations via
.Xr usleep 3 .
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "DISPLAY" -compact
.It Ev DISPLAY
Selects the X server
.Pq defaults to Li :0 No via Xlib .
.El
.Sh SIGNALS
Default disposition for all signals.
In particular,
.Dv SIGTERM
and
.Dv SIGINT
terminate the daemon without restoring the original background.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Start from
.Pa ~/.xsession :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
xbgcd &
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr xsetroot 1 ,
.Xr XSetWindowBackground 3 ,
.Xr XAllocColor 3 ,
.Xr pledge 2
.Sh BUGS
Several diagnostic strings inside
.Pa xbgcd.c
misspell the program name as
.Qq xkbcd
or
.Qq xbcd .
The binary itself is named
.Nm .
.Pp
.Nm
leaks the
.Vt Display No handle on normal exit paths because the main loop never returns; this is
unreachable in practice since the program runs until signaled.
